{
  "texts": [
    "For yes-no question answering, we choose PubMedQA (Jin et al., 2019) and Privacy Policy QA (Ravichander et al., 2019).",
    "For extractive question answering, we choose the SquadShifts dataset (Miller et al., 2020) that includes splits for the New York Times (NYT), Amazon, and Reddit.",
    "Finally, for the NLI task, we choose Contract-NLI (Koreeda and Manning, 2021) and Vitamin C (Schuster et al., 2021).",
    "We provide additional details in Appendix A.",
    "In our experiments, we focus on tasks such as question answering and natural language inference that require us to generate a question or hypothesis and an answer."
  ]
}